  "prompt": "My driving license is lost. How do I apply for a new one?",
  "response": "The process to apply for a new driving license after losing the original can vary depending on your location, but here are general steps you can follow:\n\n1. **Report the Loss**: If required, report the loss to your local police department or relevant authorities, particularly if you suspect theft.\n\n2. **Gather Necessary Documents**: Typically, you will need:\n   - Identification (passport, state ID, etc.)\n   - Proof of residency (utility bill, lease agreement, etc.)\n   - Any documents related to your original license, if available (like a copy or a number)\n\n3. **Check the Requirements**: Visit your local Department of Motor Vehicles (DMV) or transport authority website to find specific requirements for replacing a lost driving license in your state or country.\n\n4. **Complete the Application**: Fill out the application form for a replacement license. This can often be done online, but you might need to visit in person.\n\n5. **Pay the Fee**: Be prepared to pay a fee for the replacement license. This fee varies by location.\n\n6. **Take a New Photo (if required)**: Some jurisdictions will require you to take a new photo for your replacement license.\n\n7. **Receive Temporary License**: If you apply in person, you might receive a temporary license until your new one arrives.\n\n8. **Monitor the Status**: If applicable, check the status of your replacement license through the relevant online portal.\n\nMake sure to also check for any special instructions or variations based on your local laws.",
